President Muhammadu Buhari, on Monday, joined other Muslims for the Sallah celebration. While Buhari attended the Eid-el-Fitr prayer at Mambilla barracks in Abuja, Nasir el-Rufai, Kaduna governor, and Sanusi Lamido Sanusi, former Emir of Kano, prayed alongside other Muslims in Kaduna. Yahaya Bello, Kogi governor, prayed at the Muhammed Buhari Civil Centre in Lokoja, Kogi state. See pictures below. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-693984" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/FB_IMG_1651526932867.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="480" />
